**Pug Version:**  2.03
I'm writing an open source project for S3. S3 is not a real file system, so I get strings from 'objects/files'), and give it to render(). I want to be able to compile pug on S3. So this fails of course:

```
let p=`
p oh hi
include d
`
let html = pug.render(p)
console.log(html)

```

It fails because of the include. If I could use renderFile(...) on a file system I would.  So try number two:
```
const link = require('pug-linker')
const lex = require('pug-lexer')
const walk = require('pug-walk')
const parse = require('pug-parser')

let ast = parse(lex(p))
walk(ast, function before(node, replace) {
		console.log(node)
	}, {includeDependencies: true}
)

```

My plan would be to feed it a string when it needs one, I would provide it instead of the file system. I assume on 'FileReference'. But it has to work anytime I need a file, including markdown, extends, etc. 
Just like renderFile(...) but on S3.
Sadly I need some help/hints.
